## Project Identity
Varient — OSS React UI component library. Three layers: Foundation (25 Radix-powered components), Animated (30 Framer Motion components), Sections (20 full-page blocks). Copy-paste DX model — users own the code, no per-component npm installs. Owner: Piyush.

## Non-Negotiables
- TypeScript strict, zero `any` — no exceptions
- Prop naming: `isDisabled` not `disabled`, `isLoading` not `loading`, `isOpen` not `open`
- Design tokens only: `--brand-500` not `#6366f1` — never raw hex or Tailwind slate/zinc names
- `cn()` for all className merging — import from `@/lib/utils`, never concatenate strings
- Never import shadcn defaults — Varient has its own color system and token names
- Every Layer 2 animated component requires `useReducedMotion()` — non-negotiable accessibility

## Technical Accuracy
- Before calling a component complete, verify every item in DESIGN.md §10 build checklist passes
- Tailwind v4 syntax differs from v3 — verify config format before writing
- Radix UI primitives handle a11y for Layer 1 — always check Radix before building native
- Live playground (DESIGN.md §9) is required for every Layer 2 component — do not ship without it
- Layer 3 Sections compose from Layer 1 + Layer 2 only — never duplicate logic inside a section file
- Next.js 16 requires Node.js 20+; Turbopack is the default bundler

## Session Behavior
At session start:
1. Read CONTEXT.md §0 — orient to current focus before anything else
2. Check .agents/skills/ for any SKILL.md matching the current task — load it
3. If any loaded skill has `stale: true` — warn the user, recommend /update-skills

Before changes in an unfamiliar area:
- Read 2-3 existing examples of similar functionality first
- Follow patterns found, not patterns assumed
